                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18350615-1535-offence-1 t18350615-name-1021"></join>Esther Bellamy</persName> and another.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1022" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1022" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1022" type="surname" value="BELLAMY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1022" type="given" value="ESTHER"></interp>ESTHER BELLAMY</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a broker's shop in Old-street. On the 9th of June, at six o'clock in the evening, I heard a noise and went to the door—I missed a fender from inside the house—I ran out, and in Cherry-tree Alley I found the prisoner with the fender under his left arm—I collared him—he knocked me down or I did him, and we both went into the kennel—in about two minutes Sarah Garrard came, and we dragged the prisoner into her house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PERRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Who keeps the shop? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> My mother and I together—the prisoner lived near us, but not with us; he never slept in the house nor the shop—I have not been in the habit of going to fairs with him—I went once with him and my mother, and eighteen or twenty more persons—his wife was there—the prisoner was tipsy when be took the fender—he did not give it up to me; he threw it down.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1023" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1023" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1023" type="surname" value="GARRARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1023" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>SARAH GARRARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I saw the prisoner with this fender.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
